timeline.message:
Return checksum objects in column validator

ColumnMatchResult contains only a String message. It contains
text description about the discrepancy between control and test
column checksum.

Instead, returns Java object ColumnChecksum object so that they
can be programmatically accessed in Verifier.

Return checksum objects in column validator

ColumnMatchResult contains only a String message. It contains
text description about the discrepancy between control and test
column checksum.

Instead, returns Java object ColumnChecksum object so that they
can be programmatically accessed in Verifier.

Also, MatchResult.mismatchedColumns does not need to be a map.
Change it to a list.

Auto-resolve mismatched strucutured-type columns

If array element or map key/value contains floating point types,
column checksum is unlikely to match. Hence, we can allow Verifier
to auto resolve those cases.

- For an array column, resolve if the element type contains floating
  point type.
- For a map column, resolve if either key or value contains floating
  point type, the cardinality sum matches, and the key or value that
  does not contains floating point type matches.

We check each mismatched column and resolve the test case only when
all columns are resolved.

Return checksum objects in column validator

ColumnMatchResult contains only a String message. It contains
text description about the discrepancy between control and test
column checksum.

Instead, returns Java object ColumnChecksum object so that they

Compute cardinality checksum for array and map columns

Auto-resolve mismatched structured-type columns

If array element or map key/value contains floating point types, column
checksum is unlikely to match.
* For an array column, resolve if the element type contains floating
  point types and the cardinality checksum matches.
* For a map column, resolve the mismatch when both of the following
  conditions are true:
  * The cardinality checksum matches.
  * The checksum of the key or value that does not contains floating
    point types matches.
* Resolve a test case only when all columns are resolved.
